    'en_US' => '<p class="img_style"><img src="/public/site/images/conference_ojs/sociology_small1.jpg" alt=""></p>
<p style="text-align: justify;"><strong>«Journal of the Belarusian State University. Sociology»</strong> is founded by the Belarusian State University in 1997 (until 2017, as «Sociology»). The journal has been keeping the position of the country’s leading academic journal on basic theoretical and applied problems of sociology, philosophy and political science. During this time, the journal has become an authoritative interdisciplinary scientific publication in which theoretical, methodical and informational materials, the results of sociological research conducted in the Republic of Belarus, the near and far abroad countries, the chronicle of the main events of scientific life are published. The journal became a reliable platform for a bold and open conversation on the most topical issues of the day. Here, the authors who have deep knowledge and leaders of public opinion, enjoying high prestige and respect among the professional community are supported and regularly published. The pages of the publication are disputed by humanitarians and naturalists, theorists and practitioners, physicists and lyricists, where dialogue is cultivated and priority is given to arguments and facts.</p>
<p style="text-align: justify;">As a rule, in each issue of the journal are leading and widely known scientists in the world: sociologists, philosophers, economists, historians, philologists, writers, literary men, representatives of natural and human sciences, theorists and practitioners. The journal is intended for people who are not indifferent to their past, present and future. It has become a great help for lecturers, researchers, postgraduate students and students, as well as for all those who are interested in the problems of the development of modern society.</p>
